The evidence with the title 'Fiscal 50: state trends and analysis | the Pew Charitable Trusts ' says May 2, 2018  ... Medicaid is most state governments ' second biggest expense, after k-12  ... Eight states — the most in almost 30 years— lost residents in 2017 alone  ... Source of state revenue — accounting for 32.6 percent of the total in fiscal 2016 — meaning that federal budget decisions also play a key role in state budgets . 
